What I usually do is to launch the reindex with [`?wait_for_completion=false`](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/docs-reindex.html#_url_parameters_2), so that a background task gets created. The reindex call will return almost immediately and tell you the ID of the task that was created.

You can then use the [Task API](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/docs-reindex.html#docs-reindex-task-api) to check the status of the task using:

    GET .tasks/task/&lt;taskId&gt;

Even when the reindex is done, the task will stay in the index and you can check the errors if any.

It is your responsibility, though, to delete that document using:

    DELETE .tasks/task/&lt;taskId&gt;

